    "created_at": "2016-06-03T04:30:45Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-06-03T04:30:45Z",
    "body": "One possible solution is to separate the entry function from the actual implementation, i.e. splitting `electron.exe` into `electron.exe` and `somedir/electron.dll`. But it would make the architecture of Electron more complicated, and I don't think we should do that.\n\nIf you just want to make it easier to find the executable, you can simply put the app into a folder write a batch script to execute it. \n"
