    "created_at": "2016-08-31T09:20:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-31T09:23:56Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz How complicated would it be to split electron.exe into `electron.exe` and `electron.dll`?\n\nWe are hitting the same problem with the firewall prompt, which is caused by the EXE path changing every time the application updates. If `electron.exe` and `electron.dll` were separate files, and all the resources and data files were resolved relative to `electron.dll`, we would be able to optionally put all the files into a subdirectory (redirecting the DLLs using an SXS manifest, like Chrome does it).\n\nThat would allow us to update the app while running, putting the new version side-by-side with the old one. The running `electron.exe` can be renamed to `electron.exe.old` and the new version put into the same folder with `electron.exe` name (again, exactly what Chrome is doing)\n"
  },
